Global Isopropyl Laurate (IPL) Market Insights
Isopropyl Laurate (IPL) Market size was valued at USD 0.50 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.75 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Isopropyl Laurate (IPL) Market Overview
The Isopropyl Laurate (IPL) market is witnessing robust growth, with a significant increase in demand from various industries such as cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, and personal care. As of 2025, the global market value is projected to reach USD 3.5 billion, driven by its versatile applications as an emulsifier, solvent, and penetration enhancer. IPL is widely used in products such as lotions, creams, and shampoos, due to its skin-friendly properties and ability to improve the texture and spreadability of formulations. Moreover, the growing preference for natural and organic skincare products is fueling the market’s expansion. The Asia-Pacific region leads the market, followed by North America and Europe. The trend towards sustainable and eco-friendly solutions in the manufacturing of IPL is also contributing to its increasing adoption globally.

